methods.checkCompatibility:
**Incompatible overloads text - text from the first overload:**

Test compatibility of this definition with another. This definition must have all columns of the other, and the
 column definitions in common must be compatible, as defined by
 ColumnDefinition.isCompatible(ColumnDefinition).

 
 Note: unlike ColumnDefinition.isCompatible(ColumnDefinition), this method does not have an equivalence
 relation. For a stricter check, use checkMutualCompatibility(TableDefinition).

*Overload 1*  
  :param other: (io.deephaven.db.tables.TableDefinition) - comparison table definition
  :return: (io.deephaven.db.tables.TableDefinition) the minimized compatible table definition, in the same order as other
  
*Overload 2*  
  :param other: (io.deephaven.db.tables.TableDefinition) - comparison table definition
  :param ignorePartitioningColumns: (boolean) - if true, other definition may contain partitioning columns not in this
          definition
  :return: (io.deephaven.db.tables.TableDefinition) the minimized compatible table definition, in the same order as other
methods.checkMutualCompatibility:
Tests mutual-compatibility of this and other. To be mutually compatible, they must have the same
 number of columns, each matched up with ColumnDefinition.isCompatible(io.deephaven.db.tables.ColumnDefinition<?>). As such, this method has an
 equivalence relation, ie A.checkMutualCompatibility(B) == B.checkMutualCompatibility(A).

:param other: (io.deephaven.db.tables.TableDefinition) - the other definition
:return: (io.deephaven.db.tables.TableDefinition) this table definition, but in the the column order of other

Strict comparison (column-wise only).

:param other: (java.lang.Object) - - The object to compare with.
:return: (boolean) True if other is a TableDefinition and contains equal ColumnDefinitions in the same order. False
         otherwise.
methods.equalsIgnoreOrder:
Strict comparison (column-wise only).

:param other: (io.deephaven.db.tables.TableDefinition) - - The other TableDefinition to compare with.
:return: (boolean) True if other contains equal ColumnDefinitions in any order. False otherwise.
